The paper discusses a new approach for sparse representation that is specifically designed to preserve spatial relations in images. This suggests that the paper is likely to be related to computer vision (cs.CV) and image processing. Additionally, the paper proposes a modified sparse representation theory, which could be related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of two-dimensional objects and multi-dimensional data also suggests that the paper could be related to multimedia (cs.MM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
